Resizable contiguous sequence container.

Examples previously provided as snippets:

```cpp
#include <vector>

std::vector<int> values{1, 2, 3};
values.push_back(4);
values.emplace_back(5);
values.pop_back();

for (int value : values)
{
    std::cout << value << '\n';
}
```

```cpp
std::vector<Sample> samples;
samples.reserve(1024);      // capacity only; size stays 0
samples.emplace_back(1.0);
samples.resize(2048);       // size changes; new values are constructed
samples.shrink_to_fit();    // non-binding capacity reduction request
```

```cpp
std::vector<int> values{10, 20, 30};
int first = values.front();
int last = values.back();
int checked = values.at(1); // bounds-checked
int fast = values[1];       // unchecked
const int *raw = values.data();
```

```cpp
