*/

functions.longDescription:
QPluginLoader is for Qt plugin objects with metadata and interfaces. Use QLibrary for a plain exported C API.

Workflow examples retained from the previous pack:

```cpp
/*
 Use QLibrary when:
   - the DLL exposes plain C functions;
   - the DLL is not a Qt plugin;
   - you need a narrow ABI boundary with resolve().

 Use QPluginLoader when:
   - the DLL is a Qt plugin built with Q_PLUGIN_METADATA;
   - you want loader.instance() to return a QObject;
   - the host and plugin share a Qt interface contract.
*/
```

```cpp
#include <QPluginLoader>
#include <QDebug>

QPluginLoader loader("plugins/mydriver");
QObject *object = loader.instance();
if (!object)
{
    qCritical() << loader.errorString();
    return;
}

auto *driver = qobject_cast<IDeviceDriver *>(object);
if (!driver)
{
    qCritical() << "Plugin does not implement IDeviceDriver";
    return;
}

driver->start();
```

